sentence: Rosalind Theresa Cash (December 31, 1938 – October 31, 1995) was an American actress, voice artist, and singer.
Cash was the second of four children born in Atlantic City, New Jersey, to John O. Cash, Sr., a clerk, and Martha Elizabeth Cash.
In 1973, Cash played the role of Goneril in King Lear at the New York Shakespeare Festival alongside James Earl Jones's Lear.
Cash appeared on the New York-area television show Callback!, which featured musical director Barry Manilow.
Her other television credits include The Cosby Show, What's Happening!!,
Cash's films included Omega Man (1971), Klute (1971), The New Centurions (1972) with George C. Scott, Uptown Saturday Night (1974) with Sidney Poitier, and Wrong Is Right (1982).
